{{Keralahistory}} '''Ariyannur Umbrellas''' is a [[prehistoric]] [[Megalith]] burial site situated in Ariyannur in [[Kandanassery]] [[Panchayat]] of [[Thrissur District]] of [[Kerala]]. [[Archaeological Survey of India]] in 1951 declared it as a centrally protected monument. The site has six umbrella stones or mushroom stones, locally called ''Kudaikkallu''. Of them, four are intact and two are partially broken.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.asithrissurcircle.in/Monuments.html |title=ARIYANNUR UMBRELLAS |publisher=ASI Thrissur Circle. |accessdate=2013-06-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.go-kerala.com/Visit%20Kerala,explore%20the%20culture,%20which%20is%20god's%20own-pages/Arch-Index.htm |title=ARCHAEOLOGICAL SITES |publisher=go-kerala.com |accessdate=2013-06-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://sites.google.com/site/culturalcapitalofkerala/videos |title=History |publisher=Culturalcapitalofkerala |accessdate=2013-06-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.hindu.com/2005/03/04/stories/2005030410860300.htm |title=Students prepare manual on flora |publisher=The Hindu |accessdate=2013-06-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=FVsw35oEBv4C&pg=PA52&lpg=PA52&dq=Ariyannur+umbrellas&source=bl&ots=imDvYHR2FD&sig=3SUW5a_WOtnP9NXhXHC-cLhUBFw&hl=en&sa=X&ei=qWm0UfuGDoOJrAeZloCIAQ&ved=0CD0Q6AEwBDgU#v=onepage&q=Ariyannur%20umbrellas&f=false |title=A Survey Of Kerala History |publisher=A Sreedhara Menon |accessdate=2013-06-09}}</ref> ==Gallery== <gallery> Ariyannur Umbrellas DSC 0775.JPG|Ariyannur Umbrellas Ariyannur Umbrellas DSC 0766.JPG|Ariyannur Umbrellas Ariyannur Umbrellas DSC 0767.JPG|Ariyannur Umbrellas Ariyannur Umbrellas DSC 0771.JPG|Ariyannur Umbrellas Ariyannur Umbrellas DSC 0764.JPG|Ariyannur Umbrellas </gallery> ==References== {{Reflist}}
